        <h2>Pro tips for shopping <span>Marble</span>, <span>Stone</span> and <span>Surfaces</span></h2>
        <img src="src/images/blogs/210113114111image.jpg" alt="">
        <p>If you thought that building yourself a new space is the most difficult task, then you are right! With selection and curation of material being one of the most important tasks of all the processes. From the selection of the furniture to the flooring, the final assortment of the products must be precisely done with meticulous considerations to different aspects. One such product that we are here to talk about is “Marble”.</p>
        <p>The first thing that comes to anyone’s mind when they hear the word “marble” is luxury. An elegant and pricey addition to any home, it amalgamates the common usability with the touch of design. From bathrooms, countertops, floors, marble sculptures or art pieces is offered with many versatile ways to plug it with your interiors.</p>
        <p>The design of a project defines the requirement of marble one should shop for. Whether it is your mosaic art or installation on any surface, marble and stone choice should be based on your design needs. The marble and stone can be used to create design innovations that gives a luxury touch to your space. One can use granite and quartzite such as Patagonia, Dolce Vita, Dolce Feather, Taj Mahal in kitchen countertops, where some acids are used in form of cleaning agents and fruit juices. Despite these products being acidic in nature, granite helps to retain the beauty of the kitchen without any strain. Amazonite, Sodalite Blue, Black Onyx, Golden Statuario and Bianco Lasa are amongst the top picks for imperishable durability & beauty as they can be used for counter tops, highlighter walls, dining spaces and bar consoles.</p>
        <p>With the uniqueness of the vein pattern and colour a marble offers; it is suggested to buy the entire quantity at once. White marble is the perfect choice for classic to contemporary floor or wall that adds a great rich finishing touch to your interiors. Some of the marble that gives a distinctive look and feel to any space are Statuario, Michael Angelo, Thasos White, Amalfi Grey, Crema Late and Sonata Grey.</p>
        <p>Whether you design an accent wall or use it to create a ceiling mosaic, there are multiple ways to bring marble into the design but before making an immense investment, it is critical to check the marble slab you are purchasing personally to eliminate the chances of any damage like cracks, cuts, spots, holes, scratches etc.</p>
        <p>Another important point is to know the area of your floor, wall and countertops before you go for marble shopping. This not only helps you with the quantity of marble required for the project but also avoids wastage of marble and saves money. With latest innovative technology & options available, one can lay a stone in a very sustainable way.</p>
        <p>Therefore, if the above-mentioned tips are followed, one can never go wrong in transforming their plain walls into a painterly masterpiece with the use of marble and stone. It is not only a versatile surface but also adds extravagance to your interior spaces and makes it look elegant with its combination with natural materials like copper, wood etc.</p>
        <p>Go ahead and add a conventional touch and beauty to your space.</p>
